data.text:
Summary

Wipro Technologies appeared to be the Corporate Investor, which was created in 1945. The venture was found in Asia in India. The leading representative office of defined Corporate Investor is situated in the Bengaluru.

Among the most successful fund investment fields, there are Real Time, Fraud Detection. Among the most popular portfolio startups of the fund, we may highlight Opera Solutions, Drivestream, Altizon Systems. The fund has no exact preference in a number of founders of portfolio startups. If startup sums 4 or 5+ of the founder, the chance for it to be financed is low. Besides, a startup requires to be at the age of 6-10 years to receive the investment from the fund. For fund there is no match between the country of its foundation and the country of its the most frequent investments - United States.

The usual cause for the fund is to invest in rounds with 2-3 partakers. Despite the Wipro Technologies, startups are often financed by Wipro Ventures, Tola Capital, Silver Lake Partners. The meaningful sponsors for the fund in investment in the same round are Wipro Ventures, Square, SoftBank. In the next rounds fund is usually obtained by Wipro Ventures, TVS Motor Company, Radian Capital.

The fund is constantly included in less than 2 deals per year. The top amount of exits for fund were in 2019. The real fund results show that this Corporate Investor is 36 percentage points more often commits exit comparing to other companies. This Wipro Technologies works on 4 percentage points more the average amount of lead investments comparing to the other organizations. The high activity for fund was in 2016. The common things for fund are deals in the range of 5 - 10 millions dollars.

This organization was formed by Ashok Narasimhan, Azim Premji. Besides them, we counted 1 critical employee of this fund in our database.
